  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mt. Agung Volcano Hygiene Kit Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">* Critical, Mt. Agung showed more than 500 volcanic quakes per day with averaged magnitude of 3.5. With 12 km of safe zone declared by PVMBG, more signs are similar to last eruption in 1963-1964.

* 48,540 people displaced, and expect to raise beyond 60,000. There are 301 IDP Camps located in 9 regencies.

* The urgent needs ranging from ready-to-eat foods, food materials for cooking, bedding kits, drinking water, milk for kids, clothes, baby and woman diapers and other hygiene and sanitation needs, and medicine.

* ADRA Indonesia has decided to monitor and keep contacts with local ERT members, local pastors and national and local government, NGOs, and key informants for possible immediate response when the volcano erupts.</narrative>
  </description>
